This paper deals with the capacity of secret-key agreement over a wiretap channel with state parameters, which is a problem in information theory (cs.IT). It also involves the concept of wiretap channels, which is a topic in cryptography (cs.CR). The paper discusses the use of source-channel codebooks, which is a technique in coding theory (cs.CC). The paper also mentions the use of symmetric channel state information, which is a topic in signal processing (cs.SI). Finally, the paper discusses the special case of Gaussian channels with additive interference, which is a topic in multimedia (cs.MM).
